{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9392527f-b8a1-4c60-be11-fdb8b9e9bd64","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n### Authentication options (`--auth`):\n\n| Value | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (organizational) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n### Example with auth:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` for custom token-based setups. Would you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"56d5947e-8e33-4412-9854-5e36f0a9038d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":267,"requestId":"A85B:2A216C:4267E3F:48DB318:69F15653"},"id":"28aa46c2-6893-4a3b-9289-49400aa11f14","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:52:42.437Z","parentId":"e8669be6-f1e8-4f45-96ed-c1667f7a531e"}
